cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.DC

The paper proposes a game-theoretic approach to solve the joint transportation and charging scheduling problem in public vehicle systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and simulations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem also involves coordination among different entities, such as PV groups, the cloud, and smart grids, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
